flowRoot.flowPara: The goal : simplify the navigation of the application grid and increase the overall usefulness of the grid with more meaningful organization and fix the problems with the current design

The show app grid button should essentially be considered an overflow menu, the dash should be the best tool for launching relevant applications via pinning favourites and displaying recently used apps.
Pinned and running applications occupy most of the space in the dash
A new area in the dash for the a given number* of recently used applications that are not currently running or pinned as a favourite.
The benefit of having this here is that it's omnipresent in the overview so it is also present in the windows & workspaces view so recent apps can be launched quickly always.
*more than the 2 that's here for demonstration
The grid layout is customizable and user-reorderable. App icon positions can be changed, moved between pages and placed into folders via drag and drop.
Icons shift their positions to make room for the icon in drag and drop. Attempting to place the icon on top of another icon will form a folder.
Present options to change the sorting of the application grid and toggle the recent apps in the dash
Area to trigger pagination during drag and drop
